main event: A witness reported observing an unidentified flying object in the sky over Youngstown, Ohio on March 7, 1967 around 8:00 PM.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright light that appeared to be hovering in the sky.
The object suddenly accelerated and disappeared from view.
The case was reported to Project Blue Book but was classified as 'Insufficient information' due to the lack of additional details.
The report mentions that the object was not further identified.
sighted object: a bright light that appeared to be hovering
